The Federal High Court sitting in Yenagoa, Bayelsa State, has delivered the long-awaited judgement on Ese Oruru, a teenager reportedly abducted, taken to Kano State and forced into marriage by one Yinusa Dahiru, TheNation has reported. The court presided over by Justice Jane Inyang sentenced Dahiru to 26 years in prison. Jane acquitted Dahiru on Count one but jailed him five years (count two), seven years (count three) seven years (count four) and seven years, count five. The sentences, according to the judge. would run concurrently. Details shortly… Source YENAGOA - Probably made to coincide with a day being celebrated as the International Women Day, Yinusa Dahiru, alias Yellow – the alleged abductor of the 14-year-old Ese Oruru, was on Tuesday arraigned at the Federal High Court sitting in Yenagoa on a five-count charge of abduction, illicit sex and… March 8, 2016 In "Top Stories" By Sandra UmehLagos - Justice Mojisola Olatoregun of a Federal High Court, Lagos, Thursday, sentenced a former Managing Director of the defunct Integrated Microfinance Bank Ltd Simon Akinteye to four years in prison, over 166.9 million dollars fraud. The court sentenced the convict to four years concurrent term of imprisonment… February 21, 2019 In "Metro" A Federal High Court in Abuja has sentenced a former National Publicity Secretary of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Olisa Metuh to a seven-year imprisonment upon convicting him on charges of money laundering and fraud. Justice Okon Abang, announced the sentencing after delivering judgment for over six hours in the… February 25, 2020 In "News"